Link from Dashboard Widgets in Lightning Experience

Link a Dashboard Widget to a Website or Salesforce Record

After giving dashboard viewers insights about their business, drive them to take the next step by providing one-click access to Salesforce records or websites.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To link from dashboard widgets: Create and Customize Dashboards
To link from dashboard widgets in dynamic dashboards: Manage Dynamic Dashboards

Add a dashboard widget by clicking + Widget, or edit an existing one by clicking on the widget.
From the Add Component or Edit Component menu, in Custom Link, enter a link destination.

IMPORTANT
Depending on whether you link to a destination in Salesforce or to another website, the destination you enter must follow certain conventions. If you don't append https:// or http:// or www., the destination gets pasted to the end of your Salesforce orgâ€™s domain.

This convention means that linking to heroku.com takes you to https://MyDomainName.my.salesforce.com/heroku.com. To navigate to the Heroku website, enter https://www.heroku.com/.

Example: Link Somewhere Inside Salesforce
To link to the Opportunities tab, enter /lightning/o/Opportunity/list.
Example: Link to Another Website
To link to Heroku, enter https://www.heroku.com/.

If adding a widget, click Add. Or, if editing an existing widget, click Update.
Click Save.

Visit a Link from a Dashboard Widget
